questions: Is it something physical/tangible (as opposed to an abstract concept, idea, or intangible thing)?
Is it alive or was it once alive (organic material)?
Is it currently alive (as opposed to something that was once alive but isn't anymore)?
Is it derived from an animal (as opposed to a plant or other organism)?
Is it derived from a plant?
Is it something typically used as food or in cooking?
Is it a fruit or a vegetable (as opposed to a grain, herb, spice, or processed plant product)?
Is it a fruit (botanically speaking, with seeds) rather than a vegetable?
Is it typically considered sweet (as opposed to sour or savory)?
Is it a fruit that typically grows on trees (as opposed to vines, bushes, or plants)?
Does it have a single large pit/stone (as opposed to multiple small seeds or segments)?
Does it have distinct segments or sections when cut open (like citrus fruits)?
Is it typically red when ripe (as opposed to other colors like yellow, green, or purple)?
Does it have a firm, crisp flesh (as opposed to soft or mushy)?
Is it commonly associated with the phrase "keeps the doctor away"?
